If the annotation can explain the fact, answer "yes", "no" or "incomprehensible". Note: The fact will always contain exactly two blanks [A] and [B], with some examples for both.

fact:region[A] is nation in location[B]
examples[A]:Portugal / England / Tanzania
examples[B]:United Kingdom / Central America / Europe
annotation:region[A] is country in location[B]
Positive Examples.explanation: In following relationship, [region] is nation in [location], examples of [region] can be 'Portugal', 'England', 'Tanzania' and examples of [location] can be 'United Kingdom', 'Central America' 'Europe'. The annotation sentence can explain the fact so it is correct.

examples[A]:Iraq / Iran / United States
examples[B]:George W. Bush / Vladimir Putin
annotation:person[B] is urging  location[A]
